Cell.Text: [S] Oh, that's right. I keep forgetting to pick that up. Poor Kerah, such a patient woman. | Now, you're supposed to get something for your trouble, aren't you? How about some gold? People seem to like that, I notice.

Node.Caption: DialogueMarkarthCalcelmoRingTopic: I have a delivery from Kerah.

Cell.Text: To protect my research, for one. There are more cutthroat scholars out there who would steal my findings if they got the chance. | And the excavations into Nchuand-Zel are dangerous. Dwemer machines and traps still function even after thousands of years.

Yes. Their history and culture is all around us in Markarth. A race of stonecutters, artisans, and engineers. | They invented machines and built elaborate underground cities where they researched powers to rival the gods themselves. | And then, at a time we are still not sure when, they disappeared. The whole people, all at once. Leaving behind only their works.
What are you doing here? The excavation site is closed. I don't need any more workers or guards.
Nchuand-Zel? The ruins underneath Markarth? The wealth of artifacts that I've based two human lifetimes of research on?
Magic. That's what they always want. Never history. Never the secrets of the lost races. No, just little spells and enchantments.

Node.Caption: DialogueMarkarthCalcelmoChoice02: Are you a wizard? I wanted to buy some spells.

Cell.Text: I told you I'm not hiring any more guards. Why do you people always bother me when I'm trying to finish my research?

Node.Caption: DialogueMarkarthCalcelmoChoice03: I was looking for you, actually.

Cell.Text: [S] You idiot. Do you even know who I am? The most recognized scholar on the Dwemer in all of Tamriel, and you people keep bothering me! | I... I'm sorry I... I got too excited. I'm in the middle of some very... stressful work, and I shouldn't have yelled. How can I help you?
A guard said you own the Dwemer Museum.
Correct. It's a private place where I can catalog my research. Occasionally, the Jarl will come in and have questions, but that's thankfully rare.
Persistent aren't you? Oh, very well. Who am I to stand in the way of curiosity?

Node.Caption: DialogueMarkarthCalcelmoExcavationSiteTopic: I'd like to see the excavation site.

Cell.Text: I'll let you in if you agree to something for me. There's a giant spider in Nchuand-Zel. My workers call her "Nimhe," the poisoned one. | If you deal with Nimhe, I'll let you into both the excavation site and my Dwemer Museum. What do you say?
[S] Enthusiasm. Good. Here's the key to the dig site.

Node.Caption: DialogueMarkarthCalcelmoAccept: That spider is as good as dead.

Cell.Text: Oh, very well. Probably safest that way.
